message:
@MikeDerk - Did you agree with the part about the woman being a steadfast intuitive doe-er, or you think there's not enough information in the synopsis to be sure?

The reason the woman hasn't met her soulmate is external, she was never in the same town as him before, or there were a lack of interested candidates for the position in her home town.  So that's pretty clearly external.  I think that's why there has to be a bit of emphasis on the setting, because the fact that after a long time making no progress staying at home and hoping to meet a man in her everyday life she has finally decided to get off her butt and travel to "romance town", which had to happen before she could really attack the problem.  Maybe it's a prerequisite of something.

The man doesn't like children because they are annoying, which could probably be restated as disruptive, so that could be something like he wants a controlled environment and children are inherently uncontrolled.  Or I guess it could be something like children complicate an otherwise pleasantly simple life, so avoiding children is logical when he lacks a feeling to contradict it.  Either way, he specifically doesn't want children in his immediate vicinity or living with him.  And this was something he decided a long time ago and never bothers to question, so I could also see an argument for consider/reconsider there.  So, I dunno, not wanting children near him seems external but if the real problem is that he leads an unexamined life, that's internal.  Could be part of it is OS throughline and part IC throughline??
